spanGrp.span: My grandma says that when they arrived here there were no people; there was nothing.
Ys mamita t she-n jie-wa des-lo Ji wa jera ka pe ta yes' ka yor ta
all there was was a huge jungle.
ka yor kun ta kebiye r k'yaka wa jebu n sigan kom' Je wa (_) b n sigang r
My grandma says that when they arrived here, she came and her mother lived in Valle de la Estrella.
Ys mamita she (_) bete-te r jie mn je ser-g r Valle de la Estrella
She came from there to live here.
jega jie bete-te jiwa des-n jiwa s-n'
They took a place called Ogak.
Jie-wa t k' gug kie t Ogak ska
Jeska jeska jie-wa t k' kie r Saparik ska
She lived for a long time;
My grandma says that the place was different. My grandpa went to work and left her with my grandma, I mean, my mother.
Ys mam (r) mam (r) mamita t she-n k' r jaul ra ys tatiga mi-g shkabl t jie je-ge-tan ys mami (r) (_) mamita ra mama je-g-tan
He went to work far away; there was no place nearby to work.
K' kom' jan mn-n shkabl ka m shkabl-gle ta n serka n
They went to work there, far away.
Jega jie-wa mi-g-lo-n shkabl kom' wa
So, my grandma went to work with them;
Jera ys mamita b mi-g-m shkabl jie-wa ra
she would hunt the meat in the bush with the dogs.
Je t jir te-g yeke ts k' dikin te-g chichi wa
They lived just on that. In order to buy clothes, my grandpa had to go to work there.
Bik je wa jeb n wa jie-wa se-n' sua bi jir bi tu-gl-ra
Later on, many more people came to live there.
Tatiga jan mn-n jega shkabl je tgapa n kepa pe taba-n-ka se-n' se-n' jeska r (_) kennra yigira
But people say that long ago there were not so many good people here.
Ys ma/ (_) siga-wa t she-ra n ka pe ta bi
My father is from here but my grandma is from there.
Ys kaga r jiwa ta ys mamita je de r jamwa
Many came from there. Thus long ago people lived differently; the houses were different;
Je jie-wa deu-lo je wa t'i ata nyigira jebi (_) r jaul jie-wa j r jaul
they drank in calabashes, ate [their food] on leaves, but now we dont thave that.
jie-wa di yu-g r tk' n k'g jrga Ata jira sa n ka w je ta sa (r) sa ian'-w r
We have changed ourselves and only look at the whites things; glasses, spoons, plates are different.
sa t pe del b n su-g pe baso pe kuchara pe plato r jaul
Long ago they had calabashes and leaves, and ate and drank on them.
ayigira jie-wa r tk' b K'g b jrga jie-wa yug-g di yu-g
My grandma, my grandpa, my aunts, the elders lived like that.
Jebi ys (_) mamita-wa tatiga-wa sht kayeg sht kegl-wa sen-l
Long ago it used to be like that, not like it is today.
